<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Tops Investment League In Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Britain attracted more inward
investment than any other European country last year, according to
the latest research by business consultants Ernst &AMP; Young.
</P>
<P>
In 1998 UK accounted for 27 percent of all European inward
investment projects, more than three times as many as Germany,
which got 8 percent, and more than double the 12 percent gained by
France.
</P>
<P>
The UK also attracted 36 percent of investment projects from
the Far East and U.S.A., with Greater London remaining the favored
area of the country for locating business, said Ernst &AMP; Young.
</P>
<P>
Barry Bright, an official from the Invest in Britain Bureau,
said: "Where investment from outside Europe is concerned, the
advent of the euro has not overshadowed the sum of the advantages
which draw companies to the UK."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
