<HEADLINE> U.S. Congress Committee Releases Anti-China Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 25 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. House committee released an
anti-China report Tuesday, alleging that China stole nuclear secrets
from the United States. The so-called espionage case was strongly
denied by China.
</P>
<P>
This was "merely a fallacy dreamed up by a few people in the United
States with ulterior motives and in essence an attempt to stir up
anti-China feelings and divert people's attention", Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Some Americans are sticking to the Cold War thinking and are
making a great effort to dream up stories about China's spying on U.S.
nuclear technology," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The 700-page report was drawn up by a special House of
Representatives Committee chaired by Republican Representative
Christopher Cox. 
</P>
</TEXT>
