<HEADLINE> Student Enrollment Increases in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Education
Genet Zewdie said Tuesday that student enrollment at all levels of
education has grown steadily over the past few years throughout
the country.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the official Ethiopian News Agency, the
minister said the number of primary school students has increased
to nearly six million now from 1.8 million seven years ago.
</P>
<P>
She said the number of secondary school students has now
reached 467,669 from 363,686 six years back with annual average
growth rate of 5.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The annual capacity of higher educational institutions to admit
new students today stands at 12,000 as against only 6,000 a couple
of years ago, she said.
</P>
<P>
The minister attributed the rise in the number of student
population to the construction, expansion and up-grading of
schools in all regions side by side with the production and
training of new teachers.
</P>
<P>
She said 358 new primary schools have been built and a number
of others expanded while 3,449 fresh graduate teachers were
employed over the years.
</P>
<P>
Various colleges will be up-graded to the level of university
at a cost of 196.5 million birr (24.9 million U.S. dollars) soon,
she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
