<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe To Conduct Socio-economic Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 25 (Xinhua) -- The Central Statistical Office (CSO)
of Zimbabwe will conduct an Indicator Monitoring-Labor Survey from
June 1 to 14 this year and is appealing for cooperation from local
leaders and households which will be selected for the exercise.
</P>
<P>
CSO Director Lazarus Machirori told the Zimbabwe News Agency
Tuesday that the survey would be conducted under the provisions of
the Census and Statistics Act, in terms of which any information
collected would be strictly confidential and used for statistical
purposes only.
</P>
<P>
He said the objective of the survey was to provide
socio-economic indicators useful in monitoring selected aspects of
living conditions as well as providing in-depth information on the
labor force.
</P>
<P>
"The survey is based on a nationally representative sample of
about 14, 000 households in communal land, resettlement, urban,
small and large scale commercial farming areas," he said.
</P>
<P>
The survey which is done after every five years would be
conducted by field staff comprising provincial supervisors and
enumerators. 
</P>
