<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Authorizes Merger of Vodafone, AirTouch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS May 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said here
Tuesday that it has approved a merger between the British company
Vodafone Group plc and the Californian AirTouch Communications,
Inc.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) executive body said the companies' main
activity is the operation of mobile telecommunications networks.
The new company is active in most European countries either
through joint ventures or own networks and will have a combined
turnover of 10.3 billion euros (10.9 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Commission also said it has identified a competition
problem in the German market in relation to mobile
telecommunications. Both the companies are active in German market
through joint venture, E-Plus and D2 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Vodafone has agreed to sell its stake in E-Plus, which
eliminates any overlap between Vodafone and AirTouch in the German
market for mobile telecommunications, the commission added.
</P>
<P>
The commission in its investigation concluded that the relevant
geographic market for mobile telecommunication is national since
permanent roaming is currently not an economically sensible
alternative.
</P>
<P>
Based on national markets, the commission said, the merger is
largely complementary. There are only two EU member states where
the two companies are active, namely Germany and Sweden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
