<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Institute: 500 German Children Infected With HIV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN May 25 (Xinhua)--Since 1980s, some 500 German children
under thirteen have been found infected with HIV, the fatal virus
that causes AIDS, a Berlin-based institute reported.
</P>
<P>
Among them 117 have been killed by AIDS, said Robert Koch
Institute in its Epidemiologic Bulletins published on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total 37,000 HIV-infected people were living in Germany in
the end of year 1998, and 5,000 among them had been diagnosed with
AIDS, said the institute.
</P>
<P>
Every year about 2,000 Germans were newly infected with the
virus, and the speed remains the same during recent years, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Since early 1980s when the AIDS epidemic were first detected,
Germany has totally registered 17,955 AIDS patients, 11,502 among
whom have been dead.
</P>
<P>
In west Europa, there are 1.5 million people infected with HIV,
and annually more than 10 thousand are diagnosed with AIDS, said
the institute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
