<HEADLINE> "Fruitful" Henan-Guangdong Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 26 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
signed 76 projects, valued at 1.85 billion yuan, with central
China's Henan Province during two days of talks on economic and
technology cooperation which ended today in Zhengzhou, the capital
of Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
Henan Province introduced 16 name brands and 18 high
technologies from Guangdong, indicating that cooperation between
the two provinces has entered a substantial stage.
</P>
<P>
Years of effort have seen Henan set up a number of large-scale
wholesale markets, which make it possible and very convenient for
nearly 500 million people in neighboring provinces and cities to
do business locally.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Province has shown great interest in the markets in
Henan, which, on the other hand, is badly in need of technology,
expertise, funds, and information for the further development of
its local economy.
</P>
<P>
The two provinces have proposed to transfer some of Guangdong's
favorable industries like household electric appliances,
foodstuffs, electronics and garment, to Henan Province, as a way
of making full use of their advantages and ultimately to promote
their economic growth.  
</P>
