<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Karachi Stock
Exchange (KSE) plummeted by 6.55 percent on Wednesday amid panic
selling in the wake of air strikes by India in the disputed area
of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The KSE 100-share price index fell 91.28 points to 1,300.7 from
Tuesday's 1,391.98 points with a total trading volume of 210.242
million shares.
</P>
<P>
