created a new record. Earlier, the record was 279.04 million
shares registered on July 23, 1997.
</P>
<P>
"The market opened with a weak note as the news of air strikes
by India at Kargil zone on the Indian side of Kashmir forced weak
holders to resort to selling as they fear that Indo-Pakistan war
would erupt," said Shahid Rawjani, a dealer with Prudential
Securities Pvt. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
He said the market was also heavily overbought and this news
activated the sellers who thought that the economy of the country
would again derail if a war broke out.
</P>
<P>
Of the 185 active issues, losers outnumbered gainers by 128 to
20 while 37 remained unchanged. 
