<HEADLINE> Safe Working Environment Urged in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Public Service, Labor and
Social Welfare Minister Florence Chitauro Wednesday urged
organizations to invest in safe and healthy working environments
for their employees.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a National Social Security Authority (NSSA)
conference in Harare, Chitauro said adequate investment in safety
would make good business sense.
</P>
<P>
"Investment in the short term might look like a waste of
resources to many, but one has to appreciate that the net benefits
derived from accident- free business concerns are many," she said.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, organizations with sound safety
management investment and resultant good safety records were
poised to enhance their corporate images in the business world.
</P>
<P>
"While the government is calling for enterprises to embark on
environmental audits, on its part it is in the process of
reviewing all pieces of legislation which have safety and health
components," she said.
</P>
<P>
"This is with a view to finding the best way to coordinate the
management of safety and health issues in the work environment,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
It was essential that workers be protected against hazards in
the workplace if safety provisions were to have meaning, she
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
