<HEADLINE> Beckham Likely to Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- David Beckham is now expected to be
fit for Manchester United's European Cup Final against Bayern
Munich in Barcelona Wednesday evening, according to local reports
today.
</P>
<P>
The England midfielder appeared to injure his right thigh
during a training session at the Nou Camp Stadium on Tuesday,
local.
</P>
<P>
Beckham walked carefully to the sideline holding his leg for
treatment before United physio, David Fevre, placed an ice pack on
his thigh.
</P>
<P>
Beckham is expected to be given the central midfield role left
vacant by the suspensions to Roy Keane and Paul Scholes.
</P>
<P>
Some observers have suggested that Beckham's ice pack could be
a ruse to fool Bayern into thinking he would be absent.
</P>
<P>
But that suggestion is rejected by United director Sir Bobby
Charlton.
</P>
<P>
"He's very important," the 1968 European Cup winner said of
Beckham.
</P>
<P>
"It's certainly not a ploy. This is too important and we're
playing against one of the best teams in Europe.
</P>
<P>
"It's not a case of mind games or anything like that."
</P>
<P>
Phil Neville also needed treatment for a slight ankle injury
during the session.
</P>
<P>
He was able to return to action soon after, although he is not
likely to start the game anyway. 
</P>
