<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Stock Trading System Passes Y2K Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand
(SET) announced Wednesday that its computerized trading system has
passed a comprehensive test, which assesses its ability to
recognize the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The SET said in a statement that the test, conducted on May 22,
involved all connected systems and networks, including those of
member companies and subscribers to the SET's information service
systems.
</P>
<P>
While all systems tested on May 22 were 100 percent compliant,
the SET will test other related systems on June 5, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Programmed to use double digits to represent the year, many
computers would either fail to interpret the double zeros to
designate the year 2000, or would interpret them as 1900, causing
the computers to fail.
</P>
<P>
Businesses and governments worldwide have been rushing to
reprogram their computer systems before the new millennium comes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
