<HEADLINE> Aung San Suu Kyi Meets Elder Son in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Aung San Suu Kyi, general secretary
of Myanmar's opposition National League for Democracy, met her
elder son Alexander here Tuesday, according to a government
Information Sheet issued here Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Alexander, who arrived here Tuesday, is another son of Aung San
Suu Kyi coming over from Britain to meet his mother after their
father, Michael Aris, died of prostate cancer in Britain in March
this year.
</P>
<P>
The younger son, Kim, came on April 16 and was permitted to
stay for a fortnight with his mother.
</P>
<P>
When Aris was dying in Britain, Aung San Suu Kyi refused the
Myanmar government's offer to allow her to leave the country and
join her husband, fearing that once she left Myanmar, she would
not be able to come back.
</P>
<P>
Aris' visa application to join Aung San Suu Kyi in Yangon
before his death was also reportedly denied then by the Myanmar
government.
</P>
<P>
Aung San Suu Kyi was married to Aris, a British citizen, in
January 1972 in England and they have two sons. She returned to
Myanmar to see her then dying mother Daw Khin Kyi in 1988 when the
country was in a political crisis and has since then resided in
the country. 
