<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Urges G8 to promote Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 26 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Wednesday called on the Group of 7 industrial nations and
Russia to adopt policies favoring economic growth and attach
importance to development needs of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to German Chancellor Gerhard Schroder, Annan urged
them to consider more steps to protect the international financial
system against instability, to take quick action to reduce the
debt of the poorest countries and to increase aid.
</P>
<P>
Germany chairs the annual summit of the Group of 8 scheduled
for June 18-20.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he advocated the measures as recent financial crises
have reversed the economic and social gains of decades, returning
large sectors of the world population to impoverishment and
threatening to leave billion in perpetual misery.
</P>
<P>
Proposals for strengthening the international financial system
put forward by the United Nations merit serious consideration,
said Annan. He urged additional measures to prevent the recurrence
of devastating crises like those of 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
The proposals, unveiled in January, call for greater liquidity
to fight off financial contagions, regional reserve funds, debt
standstill mechanisms and closer oversight of capital markets.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. position paper also called for letting developing
countries to determine their own capital control and exchange rate
policies.
</P>
<P>
Annan said further action is needed to relieve the debt burden
of the poorest countries, most of them are in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The decline of official development assistance (ODA) should be
reversed and there is a need for innovative ways to mobilize
additional resources for development, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
