<HEADLINE> UK: 12,000 Troops on Kosovo Stand-by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain said on Wednesday that some
12,000 British troops were being put on stand-by to be ready to go
to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Defense Secretary George Robertson told parliament the exact
number Britain would deploy to Kosovo would depend on the
commitments made by other countries.
</P>
<P>
The move follows NATO's decision to double the number of its
ground troops in the Balkans to ensure that Kosovo's hundreds of
thousands of refugees can return home.
</P>
<P>
Robertson said the troops earmarked for Kosovo would be put on
shortened notice to move. They would include three infantry
battalions, three commando brigades, combat support groups and air
force support helicopters.
</P>
<P>
There are some 7,000 British troops in Balkans. NATO expects to
deploy up to 60,000 forces there.
</P>
<P>
Britain, the most hawkish within NATO, has led in the calls for
an early deployment of ground troops around Kosovo.  
</P>
