<HEADLINE> Indian PM to Visit Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari
Vajpayee will visit Bangladesh in the third week of June this
year, the BSS news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vajpayee "will arrive here on June 19," Acting Foreign
Secretary Mohiuddin Ahmed was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"His visit is linked to the inauguration of a regular bus
service between Dhaka and Calcutta," but details of the visit were
being worked out, he said.
</P>
<P>
This will be Vajpayee's first visit to Bangladesh as prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The trial run of the Dhaka-Calcutta bus service, delayed
several times, took place early last month, after the two
countries signed a two-year agreement in India in February this
year.
</P>
<P>
About 500,000 Bangladeshi nationals visit India each year and
the direct bus service would greatly reduce the hassle of the
passengers who had to undergo in the past, according to Karar
Mahmudul Hasan, joint secretary of the Ministry of Communications.
</P>
<P>
The service would facilitate movement of people and provide an
opportunity for greater interaction between the two peoples, he
said. 
</P>
