<HEADLINE> Beijing Striving To Accomplish Export Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital plans to take
effective measures to fulfill its target of achieving 2.87 billion
US dollars worth of exports this year.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Yi Xiqun, director of the Beijing Foreign
Trade and Economic Commission, at a local export boosting
conference which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be focused on re-orientating export markets,
optimizing the export mix, granting more eligible enterprises with
the rights to handle exports, and encouraging investment  abroad
and processing with exported raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Beijing will increase efforts to develop export markets in
Africa, Latin America along with western and southern Asian
regions.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to the export of computer software,
which is estimated will hit 50 million US dollars this year and
exports of vegetables, fruits and flowers.
</P>
<P>
It will encourage more powerful local enterprises to do
countrywide and trans-national businesses in the wake of such
successful examples as the Capital Iron and Steel Company and the
well-known Legend Group computer company.
</P>
<P>
The measures are expected to effectively check the export
decline which began in the early part of the year and within the
next few months, Yi added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
