<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for Regional Economic Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Myanmar commerce
official Wednesday called for stronger regional economic
integration to bring about stronger competition.
</P>
<P>
"In part, the motivation is also geopolitical," said Myanmar
Minister of Commerce Major-General Kyaw Than in his opening
address at a business forum of the Chambers of Commerce and
Industry of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Kyaw Than stated that through economic integration, regional
groupings will be better able to withstand the pressure of an
unpredictable world.
</P>
<P>
He added that such integration is in essence the hedge against
the uncertainties of the global economic environment.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there is a close relationship between trade,
investment and development, with foreign direct investment (FDI)
becoming more closely interconnected with trade in the framework
of integrated international production strategies.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to pay equal attention to controlling
capital movements wherever possible while inviting FDI to improve
the investment climate in ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that the Asian financial crisis has made
clear the necessary function of restrictions on capital movements
and on trade in times of balance of payment difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
