<HEADLINE> Crack Police Squad to Tackle Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Urumqi Customs today set up a
special police bureau in a bid to crack down on the rampant
smuggling in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
It is the biggest customs unit in China in terms of the number
of posts within its supervision. Under its jurisdiction there are
now 16 state-level category-one posts and 11 category-two posts of
entry and exit.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, customs officials have solved
nearly 100 smuggling cases, involving 170 million yuan worth of
goods.
</P>
<P>
The new police bureau will focus on fighting the smuggling of
imported goods like ammunition, explosives, drugs, automobiles,
auto parts and cigarettes, as well as other criminal and law-
breaking activities. 
