<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Out of French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia was edged out of the French Open tennis tournament
Wednesday by Dominik Hrbaty of Slovakia, 6-4, 6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, a former French Open champion, failed to touch and
flair against the 31st-ranked Hrbaty, who is unseeded at Roland
Garros.
</P>
<P>
Fans whistled and booed at Kafelnikov as he left the court
after the one hour, 47-minute match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
