<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada May Send More Troops to Balkans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Canada is considering sending more
troops to the Balkans as NATO discusses preparing for the use of
ground forces in Kosovo, said a senior Canadian official.
</P>
<P>
Art Eggleton, Canadian Defense Minister, told reporters as he
left a cabinet meeting Tuesday that increasing the Canadian
contingent is being discussed.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, we are considering that," Eggleton said. "We have made no
determination, no decision, but we are looking at the matter."
</P>
<P>
About 800 Canadian troops are reportedly on their way to the
area to join the 4th British Armored Brigade as part of a
reconnaissance group with a mandate to enter Kosovo as part of a
peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
"I understand that NATO next week, at what they call a force
generation conference, will discuss what countries can do, in
terms of additional troops for peacekeeping purposes," said
Eggleton.
</P>
<P>
"We will participate at that time and... I anticipate we will
have a decision by that time," added the defense minister.
</P>
</TEXT>
