<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Bolivian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Huang Ju, a member of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, met with a delegation from Bolivia's Leftist
Revolutionary Front led by its Chairman Oscar Zamora Medinacelli,
here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Huang, also secretary of the Shanghai Municipal Committee of
the CPC, called Zamora an old friend of the CPC and Chinese
people, and spoke highly of his contribution to promoting
friendship between the parties and people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that the delegation's ongoing China visit will
help promote the relations between the two parties as well as
mutual understanding and friendship between the people of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Zamora said that China's economic growth and social development
impressed the delegation very much.
</P>
<P>
The Bolivian delegation will leave for home Friday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
