<HEADLINE> India Test-Fires Surface-to-Air Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Following its launching of three
satellites with a single launching vehicle, India on Wednesday
also test-fired a naval version of surface-to-air missile
"Trishul" from the base of Cochin in the far-southwestern India.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's flight marked a step toward user evaluation and
induction of the missile system in the navy by the year 2000, a
Defense Ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The "Trishul" missile flies at a supersonic speed and skims
over the sea at a very low altitude and hits sea skimming missiles
aimed at Indian ships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
