<HEADLINE> 22nd UPU Congress Insured Against Mishaps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from 189
governments and more than 30 international organizations who are
expected to attend the coming 22nd Congress of the Universal
Postal Union (UPU) have been insured against any possible mishaps
during their stay in China.
</P>
<P>
A life insurance contract with a total insured amount of over
400 million yuan was signed here today between the Secretariat of
the China Organizing Committee and the China Life Insurance
Company (China Life), the biggest life insurer in China.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release by the China Life, the insurance
contract covers all the 2,000-odd formal representatives and their
accompanying partners expected at the congress. Each of them would
be insured for 200,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The 22nd congress is the last UPU congress in the 20th century
and the first of its kind ever hosted by China.
</P>
<P>
The China Organizing Committee is chaired by Vice Premier Wu
Bangguo, while President Jiang Zemin is the honorary chairman.
</P>
<P>
The congress is scheduled to open in Beijing on August 23 and
close on September 15.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
