<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 86.78 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday lost 86.78 points to 3,973.3
as against Tuesday's close of 4,060.08.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost 37.69 points to 1,719.2 from the
previous close of 1,756.89.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar indexes were quoted lower at 391.99
and 152.45 compared with the last close of 399.73 and 155.71
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities on the BSE market Wednesday suffered a sharp setback
in the wake of panic selling triggered by fears of tension between
India and Pakistan following air strikes by the Indian Air Force
in the Kargil sector of India-held Jammu and Kashmir to "clear out
Pakistan infiltrators" in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
