<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for Efforts to Avert Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Myanmar government
official Wednesday called for efforts to avert regional conflicts,
saying the threat of conflicts is still looming.
</P>
<P>
"We are living in an era of multi-dimensional strategy,"
Brigadier-General D.O. Abel, minister at the Office of the
Chairman of the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council, said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session here Wednesday of a business
forum of Chambers of Commerce and Industry of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations, Abel noted that a total of 782 regional
conflicts were registered after the end of the Second World War.
</P>
<P>
The multi-dimensional strategy involves political, economic and
military involvement, he said, adding that subjection will be
sought by using one or even all these three methods.
</P>
<P>
He added that Myanmar hopes for the best but is also prepared
for the worst. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
