<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Busy Preparing For National Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Several hundred senior citizens
aged over 60 have applied to the Dongcheng (eastern city) District
Government of Beijing to join the civilian parade on this year's
National Day, although the district's allocated quota is only 100.
</P>
<P>
The People's Republic of China will celebrate its 50th founding
anniversary on October 1 this year and the Chinese capital is
stepping up the preparations for what is expected to be the most
splendid and magnificent national day celebrations in decades.
</P>
<P>
"On October 1, a mammoth civilian parade with some 140,000
participants and a grand military parade will be staged in
Tian'anmen Square. The square will also be the site of a 100,000
people get-together and a large fireworks display in the evening,"
said an official with the Beijing city government.
</P>
<P>
The selection and training of local residents who will
participate in the parade and the get-together have been going on
for weeks, while eight fireworks manufacturers selected through
open bidding have started production, added the official.
</P>
<P>
Many local schools have introduced periods of physical exercise
for their students in order to make them fully fit for the
exhausting march through the city.
</P>
<P>
According to another source with the city government, the
renovation project of Tian'anmen Square is also progressing
smoothly, with some 1,500 square meters of new paving flags laid
every day.
</P>
<P>
"Now more than 50,000 square meters of the square has been
covered with new paving flags and the blue metal fence now
encircling the square will be dismantled soon," said the source.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
