<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 13:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Denounces U.S. Official for Anti-Iran Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi Wednesday denounced recent remarks made by
U.S. Commander in the Middle East Anthony Zinni against Iran.
</P>
<P>
Asefi said that Zinni's "irresponsible" remarks were the
result of his full lack of knowledge of the situation in the
region and an attempt to create tensions and sow discord among
regional countries, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a lecture to Britain's Royal United Services Institute on
Monday, Zinni criticized the British government for improving
relations with Iran and termed the recent promotion of
Tehran-London ties as an "over-hasty engagement with Iran."
</P>
<P>
Iran and Britain announced on May 18 to promote their
relations to ambassadorial level from charge d'affaires.
</P>
<P>
However, Zinni said that Tehran has yet to show changes on the
issues which the United States are concerned.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Iran severed their relations in 1980 following the
take-over of the U.S. embassy in Tehran by Iranian university
students in 1979.
</P>
<P>
During the past two decades, Washington has been accusing
Tehran of seeking weapons of mass destruction, supporting
terrorism and undermining the Middle East peace process. But Iran
rejected all the accusations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
