<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Law, Order Situation Improves in Southwest Bangladesh: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The law and order situation has
"remarkably" improved in the southwestern region of Bangladesh
during the past month, Home Minister Mohammad Nasim said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 33,000 identified terrorists and people accused of
different offenses have been arrested in the combing operation in
the region during the month, Nasim was quoted by the national news
agency BSS as saying.
</P>
<P>
A number of terrorists belonging to different outlawed parties
have surrendered with a huge amount of arms and ammunition to law
enforcement agencies while 150 police camps have been set up in
the region to curb terrorism and restore law and order, he
stated.
</P>
<P>
"We have been able to restore self-confidence among the people
of the region after successful operation against the terrorists,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
But Assistant Inspector General of Police Amir Khasru said on
Monday that only 32,703 alleged terrorists had been detained and
519 firearms recovered across the country since the operation
started on April 23, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Supported by the army and the Bangladesh Rifles, the police
launched the countrywide operation to combat crimes, especially in
the southwestern region where the law and order situation had been
reportedly deteriorating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
