<HEADLINE> Cape Verde FM Says to Resign Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister of the Republic of
Cape Verde, Jose Luis de Jesus has said that he would resign soon,
the Angolan news agency ANGOP reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
De Jesus made the announcement in Praia, capital of the
Atlantic islands country,Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that he had the intention after he decided
to run for the Chief Justice of the international maritime court.
</P>
<P>
De Jesus had been secretary of state for foreign affairs and
cooperation in the administration of Prime Minister Carlos Veiga
before he was appointed foreign minister in 1998.
</P>
<P>
As the executive chairman of the Community of the
Portuguese-Speaking States, de Jesus has played an active role in
the efforts to end the conflicts in Guinea Bissau. 
</P>
