<HEADLINE> Philippine Official for Peace, Order Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
Wednesday designated Anselmo Avenido as acting Interior and Local
Governments Undersecretary for peace and order.
</P>
<P>
He is the first undersecretary for peace and order designated
by Estrada.
</P>
<P>
Avenido was executive director of Philippine Center on
Transnational Crime since January 15, 1999 until this appointment.
</P>
<P>
Avenido will supervise and oversee the operations of the
Philippine National Police, Bureau of Jail Management and Penology
and Bureau of Fire Protection and Philippine Public Safety
College.
</P>
<P>
Avenido is tasked to assist interior and local governments
secretary in the planning, implementing, monitoring and evaluation
of policies and programs of the department. 
</P>
