<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ABC Launches Comprehensive Consumer Credit Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China (ABC)
announced today that it has introduced individual consumer credit
business in seven major consumer sectors.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ABC said the bank's consumer credit targets
the markets of individual residential housing, motor vehicles,
domestic durable goods, agricultural machinery, residential
housing decoration and repairs, college fees and tourism.
</P>
<P>
He said that individual consumer credit is critical to
promoting consumption, expanding domestic demand, and maintaining
the sustained and steady development of the national economy. It
is also important for commercial banks to readjust their credit
structure and improve the quality of credit assets.
</P>
<P>
He called on all the ABC branches to take individual consumer
credit business as a strategic opportunity for business
development, and make effective efforts to expand the business.
</P>
<P>
The ABC has published a procedure for managing individual
consumer credit, which defined the maturity and interest rate
involved and detailed the application methods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
