<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Marginally Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market closed
marginally higher Wednesday with blue chip industrial stocks
leading the way as bargain hunters emerged.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed up seven points at
2,918.5 points, after recovering from negative territory earlier
in the session.
</P>
<P>
The rise ended a string of five trading days of falls by the
market.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the all industrials index closed 29.0 points higher at
5,152.6 while the all resources index slipped 16.7 points to
1,127.0.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector posted modest gains with the big four all
finishing in positive ground.
</P>
<P>
Australia's biggest bank, the National Australia Bank, gained
23.7 cents to 24.848 Australian dollars, the Commonwealth Bank of
Australia surged 32.5 cents to 24.45 Australian dollars, the ANZ
Banking Group added 0.5 cents to 11.26 Australian dollars while
Westpac Banking Group was up six cents at 10.57 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector, diversified miner BHP was 34 cents
lower at 15.90 Australian dollars, global miner Rio Tinto was down
40 cents at 22.60 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index slipped again today shedding 22.1 points, or
2.44 percent, to 883.4 points while the price of gold bullion in
Sydney closed 1.80 U.S. dollars an ounce lower at 270.85 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 382.40 million shares traded worth
633.90 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Falls outnumbered rises 790 to 546, with 487 stocks steady.
</P>
</TEXT>
