<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pollution Control on Taihu Lake Proves Effective </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Certain pollution control measures
on the Taihu Lake in east China's Jiangsu and Zhejiang province
are proving effective, according to the State Environmental
Protection Administration (SEPA).
</P>
<P>
A survey, which was conducted by the SEPA and the Ministry of
Supervision on May 20 and 21, has found that relevant departments
in both provinces are doing a good job in controlling pollution in
the lake and along its banks.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that the part of lake in Jiangsu Province
almost now has no floating pollutants and the banks are also clear.
</P>
<P>
However, the survey also found certain problems in the lake's
overall environmental protection with large amounts of garbage
from freighters and fishing boats not treated. In some areas,
where large numbers of tourists and food outlets are located,
there is not enough garbage disposal and treatment facilities.
</P>
<P>
And it seem that the awareness of the need for environmental
protection is not widely spread amongst local people and tourists.
</P>
</TEXT>
