<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Slumps to Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed more
than one U.S. cent lower Wednesday as sellers offloaded the
currency on the back of softer commodities prices.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 64.83 U.S. cents, from 65.89
U.S. cents on Tuesday, after marking a 64.68 to 65.05 U.S. cent
range.
</P>
<P>
Citibank Australia head of foreign exchange Steve Schuster said
commodity prices have been unable to maintain their momentum "and
the (currency) market's been caught a bit long."
</P>
<P>
Also at the close, the Australian dollar was worth 0.6116 euro
from 0.6217 euro on Tuesday and 79.06 Japanese yen from 80.97 yen.
</P>
</TEXT>
