<HEADLINE> Pro-Israeli Militiaman Killed in south Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A member of the pro-Israeli South
Lebanon Army (SLA) was killed and another two wounded Wednesday
morning in attacks by Lebanese guerrillas in south Lebanon, the
Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The casualties occurred when a SLA military vehicle travelling
on a road in Biyeda in the western sector of the Israeli occupied
zone in south Lebanon was hit by rockets launched by Lebanese
guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Among the two injured is a militia woman who works in a SLA
checkpoint inside the border encalve, the radio quoted security
sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
In Beirut, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
later claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
The assault came apparently in retaliation for an earlier
deadly attack by Israeli troops and SLA on the group, during
which two Hezbollah fighters were killed on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The latest fatality raised to seven the number of Hezbollah
guerrillas killed in south Lebanon since the start of this
year. Nine Israeli soldiers and six SLA members were killed over
the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli forces and its ally
South Lebanon Army out of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
