<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt Extends Aid to Laid-Off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government has
facilitated the payment of around 300 million pesos (7.5 million
U.S. dollars) to workers affected by closures, Labor Secretary
Bienvenido Laguesma said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Laguesma said the government's interventions have also helped
save the jobs of thousands of workers in the face of the current
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Metro Manila office of the Department of Labor and
Employment (DOLE), through dialogues in 19 establishments, also
paved the way for the payment of another 3.5 million pesos (87,500
U.S. dollars) to hundreds of retrenched workers.
</P>
<P>
Under the DOLE's comprehensive program for displaced workers,
more than 21,200 establishment workers and rural laborers were
given direct assistance.
</P>
<P>
Apart from this, 18,981 were assisted through job counseling
and 34,177 were issued certificates for displaced workers to get
loan assistance.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Bureau of Labor and Employment Statistics (BLES)
said hundreds of workers' organizations have obtained assistance
under the DOLE's Workers Organization Development Program (WODP).
</P>
<P>
WODP seeks to help workers belonging to unions through a
productive livelihood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
