<HEADLINE> Environmental Education in University Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Green education and environmental
protection should be a priority topic in Chinese universities
according to a number of academic experts who are in Beijing this
week attending an international symposium focusing on these
important issues.
</P>
<P>
"Environmental problems and the issue of sustained development
have become a focus of concern in the international community, and
universities in China should attach greater importance to
education in that regard," said Wang Dazhong, president of the
nation's prestigious Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
The symposium opened today and experts from more than 20
universities at home and abroad are attending along with officials
from the World Wildlife Fund, the Ministry of Education, and the
State Environmental Protection Administration.
</P>
<P>
"China's universities have been engaged in environmental
education for more than 20 years, and many of them have set up
special colleges, research institutions, departments or research
centers in that regard, and established an education system to
produce undergraduates, masters and doctors in environment-related
majors," said Wang.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua was one of the leaders in green education introducing
the topic as early as 1977. Last year, it kicked off a project to
building Qinghua into a "green university".
</P>
<P>
The three day symposium is expected to hold discussions on
topics such as teaching methods in green education, the use of
multi-media and network technologies and evaluation systems for
green education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
