<HEADLINE> Female Macao Civil Servants Visit Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of female civil
servants from Macao, which returns to China on December 20 this
year after over 400 years of Portuguese rule, arrived in Beijing
today for a five-day visit to the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The 17 strong delegation was invited by the All-China Women's
Federation (ACWF), which they visited this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Gu Xiulian and Liu Hairong, both vice-chairwomen of the ACWF,
received the Macao visitors and extended a warm welcome to them on
behalf of the ACWF.
</P>
<P>
"You all look so young and energetic. This makes me believe
that the future Macao Special Administrative Region will be a
region full of vigor and vitality," said Liu.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Macao delegation Sonia Chen said that as soon
as they got off the plane, all delegation members felt a strong
feeling that they had come home.
</P>
<P>
"The upcoming return of Macao to the motherland has brought
many opportunities for the Macao people, especially the women who
account for more than 52 percent of the region's population," she
added.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will also visit several central government
ministries and the prestigious Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
As the date of return approaches, an increasing number of Macao
government officials and employees will visit Beijing for more
exchanges with the central government. A 16 member delegation of
senior Macao civil servants is also visiting Beijing this week.
</P>
</TEXT>
