<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auto Engineering Research Institute Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Qinghua
University set up an auto engineering research institute today,
thanks to a 100 million yuan donation by the China Huachen
Holdings Company, which is involved in the automobile and
information industries.
</P>
<P>
The institute will be mainly engaged in the development of auto-
manufacturing technology and automobile design, and its aim is to
technologically support China's national auto industry by
developing and designing auto products with its own intellectual
patents, according to the director of Qinghua University Affairs
Committee, He Meiying.
</P>
<P>
The institute is the first to be established by a Chinese
university with enterprise funding and is expected to boost the
national auto industry.
</P>
<P>
The benefactor is a company with diversified investments in the
information, bio-engineering, and auto industries. It is also
parent to three companies which are listed on stock markets in
Shanghai, New York and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
