<HEADLINE> Beijing To Implement Government Procurement Regulations Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital Beijing has
issued a set of regulations on government procurement aimed at
efficient management of fiscal funds.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, which will take effect as of June 1, contain
stipulations on the means of government procurement, procurement
through public biding, application for procurement, budget
management, fund settlement, supervision on procurement, and legal
responsibilities of the bidders and sellers.
</P>
<P>
Ten kinds of commodities are listed for government procurement,
including cars, limousines, motorcycles, and personal computers.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the list are equipment with per unit price of
over 100,000 yuan, labor and services, public utilities, auto
insurance, auto maintenance and any purchase worth more than 300,
000 yuan at a time.
</P>
<P>
The practice, which is based on public bidding, is designed to
provide an important safeguard to protect the interests of the
state, combat corruption and ensure economic order.
</P>
<P>
Beijing began the practice in 1997, and introduced a trial
government procurement system in 1998. By last March, the
municipal government has made purchases of over 180 million yuan
through public bidding, saving more than 20 million yuan in fiscal
fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
