<HEADLINE> Sino-Norwegian Literature Seminar Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Norwegian literature seminar,
the first of its kind, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of writers, poets, publishers from China and Norway are
attending the seminar and they will discuss a series of hot topics
such as literature and marketing and freedom in authorship.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day seminar, a number of the most influential
Chinese writers including Wang Meng, Feng Jicai, Liu Zhenyun and
Tie Ning will give speeches on freedom in authorship and Chinese
characters in fictions and films.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is jointly sponsored by the Norwegian Embassy in
China and the Chinese Writers' Association.
</P>
<P>
Sverre Bergh Johansen, Norwegian ambassador to China, said that
literature, more than other art forms, strongly strikes at
people's souls and influences their thoughts.
</P>
<P>
Writers, more than other artists, play a large part in
promoting social development, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
