<HEADLINE> China Supports Long-term Stable Growth of Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING,May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese mainland will support a
long-term stable growth in Macao, and wishes to further economic
and trade cooperation with Macao, according to Chen Bangzhu, vice-
minister of the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC).
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when meeting with a Macao delegation of
senior civil servants today.
</P>
<P>
"The future practice of "Macao people governing Macao" and high-
degree of autonomy are both an opportunity and challenge for the
development of Macao's economy," Chen said. The SETC will deal
with the economic and trade ties between the mainland and Macao by
strictly abiding by the Basic Law of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
"We support the long-term stable development of Macao," Chen
said, "And we are willing to strengthen exchanges with the
economic and trade circles of Macao and to promote bilateral
understanding."
</P>
<P>
Chen also briefed the delegation on the function of the SETC
and the current situation affecting the mainland's economy and
market.
</P>
<P>
Ho Veng On, head of the delegation made up of 16 senior
officials from 13 major departments of Macao, expressed his
confidence over the bright future of Macao since its first elected
executive chief has been appointed by the Central Government.
</P>
<P>
Ho attributed the new changes he had observed on the mainland
to the powerful leadership of the Central Government and the
economic policies that meet and suit China's needs.
</P>
<P>
China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Macao on
December 20, ending over 400 years of Portuguese rule.  
</P>
</TEXT>
