<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak FM Calls for Restraint on LoC Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister Sartaj
Aziz said Wednesday that the escalation of firing by the Indian
side along the Line of Control (LoC) in the disputed Kashmir
region is against the spirit of the Lahore Declaration.
</P>
<P>
"Both sides should exercise restraint," Aziz said here during
his talks with reporters, adding that "we don't know why India has
escalated its firing on LoC."
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here Wednesday from Kashmir, the
Indian side launched air strikes with jet fighters and helicopter
gunships on three positions against the "Muslim militants" on the
Indian side along the LoC.
</P>
<P>
Tension between India and Pakistan is soaring these days
because of the intense artillery dual that is now going on
uninterrupted for more than two weeks along the LoC in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said that "Pakistan is showing restraint to avoid further
escalation of the situation."
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan is retaliating and will retaliate if our positions
are targeted," Aziz said. "We will take every necessary action to
defend our positions."
</P>
<P>
When asked about the telephone call to Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif by Indian caretaker Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee
Monday, Aziz said, "We are assessing the situation and will
respond to this telephone call likely today (Wednesday)."
</P>
<P>
Media reports quoted Vajpayee as saying that India will not
allow any more cross-border attacks in Kashmir. He claimed that
about 400 Muslim fighters intruded into the India-held part of
Kashmir this month.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan has called for a
halt to clashes between Indian and Pakistani troops in the
disputed Kashmir region.
</P>
<P>
Annan, who is currently visiting Sweden, Tuesday called on
India and Pakistan to "exercise restraint and cease the fighting
which has reportedly caused a number of casualties to the civilian
population and displaced others from their villages in the area,"
a U.N. statement said.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said Pakistan has agreed in principle that the two
countries should hold expert-level talks on peace and security
issues before the Indian general elections and the foreign
secretary-level talks should be held after the polls.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister also said that the Indian deputy high
commissioner was summoned to the Foreign Office Monday and was
told that firing on the LoC is against the spirit of the Lahore
Declaration signed by the prime ministers of India and Pakistan in
February this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
