<HEADLINE> Second Runway of HK Int'l Airport in Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The second runway of the Hong
Kong International Airport was officially put into use here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region said at the opening ceremony that the day "
marks an important milestone of the Hong Kong International
Airport" since it is the first time in the history of Hong Kong
that two runways operate simultaneously at its airport.
</P>
<P>
The second runway will immediately relieve peak hour congestion
and will greatly reduce the waiting time of aircraft.
</P>
<P>
With the second runway becoming fully operational in August,
this will offer additional landing and take-off slots which will
enable airlines to achieve maximum operational efficiency and will
enhance passenger convenience.
</P>
<P>
Chan said that the additional capacity of the second runway
will facilitate the further development of the extensive air
services network serving Hong Kong and will strengthen Hong Kong's
position as an international and regional aviation hub.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong International Airport, located at Chek Lap Kok on
Lantau Island 25 kilometers west of Hong Kong island, was opened
on July 6, 1998. The airport has won acclaim for its quality
services despite some chaos during its initial period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
