<HEADLINE> Nigerian Army Leader Rebukes Abacha Wife's Allegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Chief of General Staff Vice
Admiral Mike Akhigbe has rebuked a statement of the wife of former
military ruler Sani Abacha that the deceased head of state made
decisions on a collective basis.
</P>
<P>
The vice admiral, who had served as Chief of Naval Staff under
Abacha's regime, told a valedictory press conference in Abuja
Tuesday that the claim by Abacha's wife is groundless.
</P>
<P>
"It depends on what aspect. We collectively agreed to return
to civil rule," the Daily Times newspaper quoted the senior
officer as saying. "But some decrees were later churned out."
</P>
<P>
"You are also living witnesses when all the five political
parties returned one single presidential candidate for election",
he said.
</P>
<P>
Akhigbe said he had spoken at every turn in the affairs of
state and vowed not to associate himself with policies and
decisions which he did not take part in making.
</P>
<P>
On the outgoing government's stacked deficits, the vice admiral
said that the reserves were depleted by inadequate resources
inflow from the sale of oil, the need to keep international
obligations, payment of contractors and suppliers, as well as the
instability in the Niger Delta among others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
