<HEADLINE> 2 Hezbollah Guerrillas Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Two guerrillas of the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, were killed overnight
in conflicts with Israeli forces in south Lebanon, the Voice of
the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The two dead fighters, Hasan Haik and Ahmad Ali Rida, both
unmarried and aged at 73, will be buried in a funeral held by
Hezbollah officials and it supporters in the country's southern
coast city of Sidon Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The fatality raised to seven the number of Hezbollah
guerrillas killed in south Lebanon since the start of this
year. Nine Israeli soldiers were killed over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli forces and its ally
South Lebanon Army out of the country. 
</P>
