<HEADLINE> New Wave of Kosovo Refugees Flood into Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A new wave of Kosovo refugees has
occurred at the border crossings between Yugoslavia and Macedonia
over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
According to the Macedonian news agency MIA, 13,222 from Kosovo
entered Macedonia in the 24 hours from 7 a.m. Monday to 7 a.m.
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the new comers, 11,742 crossed into Macedonia through the
Blace border point, 1,214 through Jaznice and 266 through
Tabanovce.
</P>
<P>
This new influx of refugees brought the total number of Kosovo
refugees in Macedonia to more than 263,000.
</P>
<P>
Due to resource shortage and insufficient international aid,
only about two fifths of the refugees are accommodated at seven
refugee camps in Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian government has asked the Western countries to
take the refugees and reduce the burden on it.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,161 refugees were taken by planes to Italy, Sweden,
Norway and Britain on Monday.
</P>
<P>
About 300 refugees left for Norway and Portugal on Tuesday
morning and another 14 flights were scheduled for the day.
</P>
<P>
So far 66,991 Kosovo refugees have been transferred to
countries including Norway, Italy, Germany, Sweden, Holland,
France, Britain, Ireland and the United States, the MIA said.
</P>
</TEXT>
