<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Breeds New Crop Varieties With Nuclear Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- China has bred over 510 new crop
varieties with nuclear technology, accounting for a quarter of the
world's total.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Jiang, vice secretary-general of the China Isotope and
Radiation Industry Association, said the maximum yearly planting
area of the new varieties has reached nine million hectares.
</P>
<P>
"They add about four million tons of grain, cotton and edible
oil every year to the country's total output, producing some 3.3
billion yuan of profit," he said.
</P>
<P>
Nuclear technology has been widely used in agriculture in China
to raise the production of crops and livestock, and food safety
and quality. It also helps reduce pollution caused by food and
agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
"Years of research show that the new varieties pose no harm to
the human health," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He added that China has used nuclear technology to help local
residents make full use of resources in feed production, raise the
breeding efficiency of livestock and prevent animal diseases.
</P>
<P>
China has also successfully conducted small-scale tests on
eliminating fruit flies with nuclear technology.
</P>
<P>
In addition, nuclear technology has raised the efficiency of
nitrogenous fertilizer by nearly 20 percent in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
