<HEADLINE> Armed Conflicts Intensify in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The forces of faction leader
Hussein Mohamed Aidid and those of the Rahanwein Resistance Army
(RRA) have been intensifying their attacks against each other over
the control of regional capital town of Baidoa and some 25 people
were killed in the conflict.
</P>
<P>
The most serious fighting so far between the two sides flared
up Tuesday afternoon at El-Don and at Munawir just 12 and three
kilometers respectively north of the important town.
</P>
<P>
According to confirmed sources, the attack in which more than
20 battle wagons were involved has been launched by the forces of
Aidid on the militia base of the RRA at El- Don.
</P>
<P>
There are no exact casualty figures available, but sources
received through the VHF radio indicate that more than 25 people
from both sides were killed and as many as 50 others were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The RRA spokesman in Mogadishu, Mohamed Ali Aden Qalinleh, told
the press Wednesday morning that his men have defeated what he
called the coalition forces of the Oromo and Aidid's men in the
fighting Tuesday by killing 35 of them on one spot.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time that foreigners were involved in the
fighting between the Somali clans over the control of Baidoa town,
Qalinleh noted.
</P>
<P>
However, residents in Baidoa have not confirmed the presence of
any Oromo fighters in the fighting for the town.
</P>
<P>
According to independent and informed sources, the RRA forces
have captured a double-barrel anti-aircraft heavy machine gun
mounted on a four wheel drive lorry belonging to Aidid's forces.
</P>
<P>
Qalinleh claimed that his forces have likewise captured 60
assault rifles from what he called the aggressors, a claim
disputed by eyewitness in Baidoa.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitnesses confirmed that Aidid's men have lost seven
rifles to the RRA.
</P>
<P>
Qalinleh admitted that five of the RRA fighters were killed and
seven others wounded.
</P>
<P>
There was no comment from Aidid's side.
</P>
<P>
It is not known what intensifies the fighting for the control
of Baidoa at this moment, but there had been rumors that Aidid's
faction is bringing a new consignment of Somali bank notes which
are to land at the airport of the town.
</P>
<P>
Even though there has been no official word from Aidid's side
over the arrival of the money, still the faction leader himself
accompanied by dozens of battle wagons remain stationed in the
town since last week, trying to dislodge the RRA bases surrounding
Baidoa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
