<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh China Wuqiao
International Acrobatics Art Festival is expected to be held
between October 30 and November 8 in this capital city of north
China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Known as the cradle of acrobatics, Wuqiao is home to many world-
renowned acrobats and a number of them have become famous
throughout many Asian, European and American countries.
</P>
<P>
Performers from more than ten countries are expected to take
part in the festival this year, and another 20-odd countries are
applying to perform. To date, more than ten Chinese acrobatics
troupes have submitted their candidates programs.
</P>
<P>
The art show is held every two years and the earlier six
festivals have featured more than 300 programs performed by
acrobats from 26 nations.
</P>
<P>
This year's festival is to be jointly sponsored by the Ministry
of Culture and the Hebei provincial government. 
