<HEADLINE> Share Prices Edge Down on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices edged down on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday following Wall Street's second
straight day of losses.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index slid by 2.48 points to end at
1,893.73 points,
</P>
<P>
Total turnover contracted to 1,066.48 million shares worth
1,086.02 million Singapore dollars (628.12 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 267 to 84 with 93 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
GES topped the volume list of the day with a turnover of 45.34
million shares. It was followed by Popular which had 30.83 million
shares done. InnoP was the next with 28.64 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
OUB F and Tong Meng led the ascent of the day picking up 50
cents to close at 9.55 and 2.80 Singapore dollars respectively.
SembLog rose by 43 cents to finish at 5.05 Singapore dollars.
Creative 50 and DBS F climbed up 40 cents to end at 22.30 and
17.70 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Goodwood led the losers of the day, incurring
a loss of 100 cents to close at 25.00 Singapore dollars. SPH sank
80 cents to finish at 24.20 Singapore dollars. GE Life retreated
40 cents to end at 12.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that share prices nudged lower at open but later
bargain-hunting, especially in property stocks, erased some of
early losses and offset the impact of the slide in U.S. stocks.
</P>
<P>
They said that foreign investors stayed on the sideline in the
absence of fresh news and on the perspective that some blue chips
may have become overvalued.
</P>
<P>
They also said the government's renewed efforts to get the
financial sector consolidate have incurred re-emergence of the
speculation on bank takeover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
