<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Should Maintain Only Defense Policy: CPPCC Official (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A leading official of the
Subcommittee of Foreign Affairs of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) said here today that Japan should
adhere to its Peace Constitution and maintain a defense-only
policy.
</P>
<P>
The official made the remarks after the Japanese Senate passed
new Japan-U.S. defense cooperation guidelines. Its House of
Representatives had already approved the documents despite of the
opposition of the Japanese people and the Asian people.
</P>
<P>
Japan should continue on the path of peaceful development and
implement its own commitments, he said, calling the increased
Japan-U.S. military cooperation and expanded military role in the
Asia-Pacific region a serious step, one that worries the Chinese
and countries and regions in other parts of Asia and makes them
uneasy.
</P>
<P>
The key point of the documents, which were formulated by the
Japanese and U.S. governments and approved by the Japanese Diet,
is stronger military cooperation, he explained.
</P>
<P>
They empower the Japanese self-defense forces to leave Japanese
territory and cooperate with the United States in military
operations in the guise of "safeguarding regional security", but
will in fact threaten the peace and stability of the region.  (
more)
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
