<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Air Force (IAF) Wednesday launched a series
of air strikes to "clear Pakistan-backed infiltrators" in Kargil
sector of India-controlled Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The IAF used various aircraft including fighters and
helicopters from various bases to strike in Drass, Batalik and
other regions in the sector, official sources said here. Indian
caretaker Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee, who had spoken to
his Pakistani counterpart Nawaz Sharif over telephone Monday, has
warned Pakistan that "all possible steps" would be taken by the
government to "clear our territory of intrusion". (India-Kashmir-
Airstrike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ALMA ATA -- Turkmenistan is to pull out of a treaty with Russia
later this year on the joint protection of the Central Asian
republic's southern border with Iran and Afghanistan, said a
report reaching here Tuesday from Ashgabat, capital of
Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The treaty was signed between Turkmenistan and Russia in
December 1993. Under the treaty, any side which wants to leave the
treaty is required to present a note to the other side six months
in advance. Turkmenistan's Foreign Ministry confirmed it has
already submitted the note to Russia, saying it plans to quit the
treaty on November 19. Vladimir Konovalov, head of the Russian
border guards in Turkmenistan, said Turkmenistan's decision was "
reasonable," because "the Turkman border service has been fully
formed and is capable of guarding the border without Russia's help.
"(Turkmenistan-Russia-Treaty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SOFIA -- Bulgarian Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev on Tuesday
urged an early end to the Kosovo conflict, saying Bulgaria
supports a proper and effective settlement of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ananiev expressed his country's stance at a meeting of vice
defense ministers from East and South European countries, with U.S.
representatives present. The minister was quoted by the Bulgarian
state news agency as saying that "investment" in the Balkans
should not be limited to political and military areas, but should
first of all cover social and economic fields. (Bulgaria-NATO-
Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Li Zhaoxing, Chinese ambassador to the United
States, said Tuesday that the purpose of the U.S. congressional
report about so-called China's "theft" of nuclear secrets is to
slander China and derail the bilateral relations which are
important to the peoples of China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
"The allegations are sheer fabrications out of ulterior
political motives," Li said in a CNN interview. A special U.S.
House committee headed by Republican lawmaker Christopher Cox
issued an 872-page report Tuesday, asserting that China obtained
secret information on seven nuclear warheads and the neutron bomb
in "two decades of espionage" at U.S. nuclear weapons laboratories.
(US-China-Ambassador) 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
