<HEADLINE> Jordanian King to Meet Arafat in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein
is expected to visit the Gaza Strip Wednesday to brief Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat on his just-concluded European and North
American tour.
</P>
<P>
During the one-day trip to Gaza, Abdullah will also discuss
with Arafat bilateral ties between Jordan and the Palestinians and
recent developments concerning the Middle East peace process,
Jordanian officials said.
</P>
<P>
The monarch`s visit to Gaza itself is a sign of Jordan`s
support for the Palestinian people, Radio Jordan said.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process, particularly the
Israeli-Palestinian track, had been high on the agenda of
Abdullah`s three-week visits to Germany, Britain, Canada and the
United States earlier in May.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian ruler had reaffirmed the rights of the
Palestinian People, including setting up an independent state, and
called for just and comprehensive peace in the Middle East during
his talks with Western leaders.
</P>
<P>
He also tried to persuade the United States and other countries
to pardon nearly half of his kingdom`s debts of some 6.8 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah is also expected to visit Tunisia, Algeria, France and
Italy in the coming weeks on bilateral ties and regional issues.
</P>
</TEXT>
