<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 07:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Chief to Discuss Kuwaiti POWs in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) Secretary
General Esmat Abdel-Meguid said that he would go to Iraq soon and
discuss the outstanding problems between Iraq and Kuwait,
especially the issue of Kuwaiti and third country detainees in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In remarks to the Kuwaiti Arabic daily Al-Seyassah published
Wednesday, Abdel-Meguid expressed hope that his visit to Iraq
"will be fruitful and beneficial, especially that Iraq will chair
the next AL meeting in September."
</P>
<P>
He also called for an immediate solution to the issue of over
600 Kuwaiti and third country nationals allegedly still held in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Iraqi side to reveal the whereabouts of the
prisoners of war (POWs), the missing and detained people and to
present evidence on those who have died if there are any.
</P>
<P>
The AL chief stressed that Kuwait has the right to ask for its
POWs, adding that he could feel the extent of sorrow and grief of
the POWs' families during his visit to Kuwait last February.
</P>
<P>
The POWs issue, which Abdel-Meguid termed as a priority of the
AL's agenda, dominated his talks with Kuwaiti leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
