<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS-Rpt with correction Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade With U.S., Canada, Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts and
figures about China's foreign trade with the United States, Canada
and Australia in January-April of 1999, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-U.S. trade volume amounted to 16.88 billion U.S.
dollars, up 8.4 percent from a year earlier. Exports rose 7.9
percent to 11.22 billion U.S. dollars while imports grew 9.5
percent to 5.67 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-Canadian trade volume grew 12.5 percent to 1.37 billion
U.S. dollars. Exports went up 18.5 percent to 688.82 million U.S.
dollars and imports climbed up 6.9 percent to 678.96 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-Australian trade volume reached 1.69 billion U.S.
dollars, up 14.6 percent. Exports rose 8.1 percent to 735.13
million U.S. dollars while imports jumped 20.2 percent to 952.58
million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
