Turkish bases for air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
A total of 54 American and 18 Turkish fighter jets are to be
stationed in the military bases in Bandirma, Balikesir and Corlu
in western Turkey in a bid to launch attacks on the targets in
Yugoslavia from Turkey via an air corridor which Bulgaria opened
for NATO.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- The so-called "Kurdistan National Congress" convened Tuesday
in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, aimed at bringing all the Kurdish
groups and parties together.
</P>
<P>
