<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill 19 People in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people were killed Tuesday
in two separate road accidents in Rift Valley Province, western
Kenya, the East African Standard newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In Kaitui trading center, 25 kilometers from Kericho district
town, 15 people died on the spot when a bus they were traveling in
and a lorry collided head-on, according to Kericho police boss
Alfred Ouma.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred along the Kericho-Kisumu road left scores
of others seriously injured including the bus driver. They were
admitted into local hospital, still in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Benedict Mbandu, a survivor who was in the bus, alleged that
the lorry driver was to blame as he was driving on the wrong side
of the road.
</P>
<P>
Another accident occurred in the afternoon along the
Bungoma-Mumias road in the same province, killing four people
instantly as a pick-up vehicle had a head-on collision with
another vehicle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
