<HEADLINE> Malawi Sees Good Harvest This Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Malawi is expected to have a harvest
of maize crop this season with the help of good rains and
alleviate its chronic food shortages in the southern African
country.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's Zambia Daily Mail newspaper quoted Malawi's
agricultural officials as saying the country expected to harvest
2.3 million tons of maize this season, up from 1.8 million tons in
the previous one.
</P>
<P>
This will free save the foreign-exchange-thirst country from
importing maize from Zimbabwe and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Malawi's Minister of Agriculture and Irrigation, Aleke Banda
also attributed the harvest to the government's Starter Pack
Program which provides input loans for small farmers.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the government has distributed at least
24,000 tons of fertilizer and 2,429 tons of seed in this season.
</P>
</TEXT>
