<HEADLINE> URGENT: Indian Air Force Strikes Kargil Area, Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Indian Air Force (IAF) Wednesday
launched a series of air strikes to "clear Pakistan-backed
infiltrators" in Kargil sector of India-controlled Jammu and
Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
IAR used various aircraft including fighters and helicopters
from various bases to strike in Drass, Batalik and other regions
in the sector, official sources said here.
</P>
