high alert in the wake of the air strikes.
</P>
<P>
Indian caretaker Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee, who had
spoken to his Pakistani counterpart Nawaz Sharif over telephone
Monday, has warned Pakistan that "all possible steps" would be
taken by the government to "clear our territory of intrusion".
</P>
