<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Postcards for World Philatelic Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The State Postal Bureau today
issued a set of two souvenir postcards in Beijing to mark the
forthcoming China 1999 World Philatelic Exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The postcards depict the exhibition emblem and its mascot and
were drawn by well-known stamp designer Ren Yu.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jiawei, vice-director of the exhibition organization
committee secretariat, said that the State Postal Bureau usually
issues souvenir postcards for special events and to celebrate
important figures.
</P>
<P>
China will host the world's largest philatelic exhibition from
August 21 to 30 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
To mark the event the bureau has also issued a stamp of
featuring the Yellow Mountains and a letter card which focuses on
the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the All-China Philatelic Federation,
the bureau plans to issue another commemorative stamp on August 21,
the opening day of the exhibition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
