<HEADLINE> Vegetable From Inland North China Sell Well Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in
northwest China exported 200 tons of dehydrated onions last year
to Europe and Southeast Asia and exports are expected to climb to
1,500 tons this year.
</P>
<P>
To expand its production, the Zhenshanmei Foodstuffs Co. Ltd.,
a Sino-foreign joint venture in the region, has imported drying
technology from the United States and techniques from Italy. It
has also built a dehydrating production line that is one of the
most advanced in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, north China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region supplies
pollution-free asparagus, medlar, and liquorice to more than 70
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The region has spent 10 billion yuan importing up-to-date
technology and equipment to develop new products with a world-wide
market and local enterprises have developed dry white wine and
various other products that sell well abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
