<HEADLINE> Satellite Positioning Buoys In Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A group of newly developed hi-tech
satellite positioning and computerized buoys have been put into
use in the East China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Designed and built by Chinese scientists and with a total
investment of over a million yuan, the buoys have highly developed
technical functions.
</P>
<P>
The major controlling facility of this lightweight system is
composed of computers, which makes it convenient to mend and
replace those that break down.
</P>
<P>
Using satellite positioning technology, the buoys are able to
transmit data reliably and accurately.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believe that the buoys, mainly used in the
country's oceanic telecommunications networks, will be of enormous
benefit to society and the economy. 
</P>
