<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt to Restructure Power Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will push
through with the privatization of the National Power Corporation
(Napocor) and the restructuring of the power industry, the
Philippines News Agency said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the government's efforts to make the
economy more competitive in the years ahead, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Senior Deputy Executive Secretary Ramon Cardenas was quoted as
saying the government will have to tackle difficult economic
problems, such as the privatization of the Napocor, to make the
economy more competitive.
</P>
<P>
"With our present cost of power as reportedly the second
highest in Asia, we have to open up the industry and introduce
more competition, specifically in the areas of power generation
and distribution," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cardenas ruled out subsidies for the power industry, saying
this would simply aggravate the Napocor's total indebtedness.
</P>
<P>
Encouraging competition in the power industry would pave the
way for lower electricity rates, which in turn will benefit not
only residential consumers but industrial users as well, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
