changes to its route network and would make a final decision later
this year, Victory Nosi, the head of corporate communications,
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Business Day:
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa ran an unprecedented 112 million U.S. dollars
surplus in its trade with the U.S. in the first quarter of this
year as low growth translated into slumping imports of American
goods in virtually every category, according to new data of the
U.S. Commerce Department.
</P>
<P>
Sowetan:
</P>
<P>
-- South African President Nelson Mandela, due to retire after
June 2 elections, and his deputy Thabo Mbeki, the
president-in-waiting, are considered the most popular leaders by
all South Africans, Opinion '99 available Tuesday shows. 
</P>
