<HEADLINE> Singapore Prime Minister to Visit U.S., Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong will make a working visit to California and Florida of the
U.S. from May 26 to 31, 1999, and this will be followed by an
official visit to Argentina from June 1 to 3 this year, the Prime
Minister's Office announced in a statement Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said during his stay in California Goh will meet
with local officials and business leaders and visit the Silicon
Valley.
</P>
<P>
High on his itinerary during Goh's visit to Florida is his
visit to Tampa Bay Water Authority where he will be briefed on
water supply diversification and water desalination technology,
the statement said, adding Goh will also meet prominent political
and business leaders in Miami.
</P>
<P>
The visit to California and Florida is his second tour of U.S.
within an eight-month period. Goh made his last trip to the U.S.
in September last year.
</P>
<P>
On Goh's visit to Argentina, the first by a Singapore prime
minister, the statement said Goh's trip will reciprocate Argentine
President Carlos Menem's visit to Singapore from February 21 to
22, 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the prime minister's absence, Singapore Deputy Prime
Minister Lee Hsien Loong will be the acting prime minister.
</P>
