<HEADLINE> Corrupt Chinese Grain Officials Being Exposed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi Province in north China has
declared war on official misconduct in the grain business and is
straightening out the grain industry and penalizing them.
</P>
<P>
The province has dealt with 93 acts of official irregularities
in the grain procurement, reserve and distribution sector 1998 and
97 officials have been penalized, some of them with disciplinary
warnings, some being expelled from the Party or from their
official position, and some brought to court.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial government official, irregularities
in violation of State Council regulations on grain procurement
account for the bulk of the case. Some officials took bribes by
issuing fake invoices and certificates.
</P>
<P>
The misappropriation of state funds for grain procurement has
been harshly dealt with. One accountant in the Yongji city grain
bureau was sentenced to three years in jail for lending more than
280,000 yuan of state funds to an individual.
</P>
<P>
Officials in state grain enterprises have also been penalized
for the mismanagement of state procurement funds and fraudulent
activities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
