<HEADLINE> Nuclear Technology Widely Used In Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Nuclear technology has been widely
used in medicine in China, playing an important role in
safeguarding the public health and preventing the spread of
diseases.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Jiang, vice secretary-general of the China Isotope and
Radiation Industry Association, said today that China has some 4,
500 nuclear medical researchers, including 2,000 doctors and 2,500
technicians.
</P>
<P>
These personnel and the country's 800 nuclear medicine research
and application institutes, three nuclear medicine research
centers located in Beijing, Shanghai and Wuxi, carry out nearly 61
million operations on patients each year.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that radioactive nuclide molecule technology has been
applied in diagnosing tuberculosis, hepatitis, breast cancer and
hereditary diseases.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, radioactive immunity analysis has been utilized in
detecting hepatitis B carriers and tumors in cancer sufferers.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the utilization of nuclear technology in the
country's medical institutions has been safe due to strict control
and systematic administration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
