<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Declares Vesak Week to Mark Buddha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has declared the week
from May 27 to June 2 as "Vesak Week" to mark one of the most
significant days for Buddhists all over the world, officials said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vesak Full Moon Day which falls on May 29 this year is the day
of the birth, enlightenment and passing away of the Lord Buddha.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Buddha Sasana has instructed that all meat
stalls will be closed for the week and liquor outlets will be
closed on May 29 and 30.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has an estimated population of 18.8 million, of which
69 percent are Buddhists.
</P>
<P>
Several events to mark "National Vesak Festival 1999" has been
organized by the ministry and the Colombo Municipal Council.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition of Buddha relics, Vesak decorations competitions,
and an all island Vesak lantern competition are among the
activities organized to mark the event.
</P>
<P>
A "Vesak Bakthi Gee" (Buddhist Carols) competition is also to
be held in Colombo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
