in January-April of 1999, provided by the General Administration
of Customs.
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-German trade volume reached 4.61 billion U.S. dollars,
up 18.8 percent from that of 1998. Exports increased 2.3 percent
to 2.23 billion U.S. dollars while imports jumped 39.7 percent to
2.38 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
