dollars, up 29.4 percent from the 1998 figure. Exports declined 1.
3 percent to 799.18 million U.S. dollars while imports soared 66.4
percent to 1.12 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The Sino-Dutch trade volume amounted to 1.84 billion U.S.
dollars, down 2.7 percent. Exports went down 5.3 percent to 1.55
billion U.S. dollars while imports grew 14.5 percent to 285.12
million U.S. dollars.  
