<HEADLINE> Concise Edition Of Comprehensive Chinese Dictionary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- a concise edition of the
Comprehensive Chinese Dictionary was released here recently.
</P>
<P>
The 12-volume Comprehensive Chinese Dictionary, which was
published in 1994 in its original form with complex Chinese
characters, has 375,000 entries, and took 18 years to compile.
</P>
<P>
The concise edition reduces all this to two volumes mainly by
deleting some rarely-used characters and illustrations. It
contains over 20,000 entries, all in simplified Chinese characters.
</P>
<P>
Specialists say that the new edition is both authoritative and
convenient and will be especially helpful to ordinary readers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
