<HEADLINE> Colombian President Insists on Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Colombian President
Andres Pastrani said on Tuesday that his government has proposed
to undertake peace without conditions or pressures.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana insisted the national government's position would not
change regarding the kidnapping of Piedad Cordoba, a senator from
the opposition Liberal party, by the Self-Defense Paramilitary
groups (AUC) last Friday in Medellin.
</P>
<P>
"The reconciliation process between Colombians must be
unconditional and without the use of force. For that reason, the
kidnapping of whatever citizen or person of authority, will be of
no use in influencing government decisions," said an official
statement released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cordoba, a member of the peace commission and president of the
Commission on Human Rights in congress, was kidnapped by a unit of
about 15 armed persons when she visited a sick friend in a
Medellin clinic in the northeast of the country.
</P>
<P>
The government on Tuesday called on the AUC to immediately
release the senator and let her return "to her home." 
