<HEADLINE> Foreign Experts Play Active Role In Chinese Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 80,000 foreign experts
come to work in China every year in all kinds of jobs in industry,
agriculture, transportation, finance, medicine, and tourism,
according to a State Administration of Foreign Experts Affairs
official.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 740,000 foreign experts in all from more than 50
countries and regions have worked in China since the late 1970s,
according to Luo Weilin, who is in charge of the administration's
Economy and Technology Department.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has done its best to provide them with
favorable living and working conditions and to protect their
rights in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Their technology and expertise have brought good results, Luo
said. One Japanese expert who is above 80, for example, has helped
save work and improve rice yields in northern China by 10 to 20
percent with growing techniques he introduced a decade ago. The
technique is now being used all over northern China and even in
some southern areas.
</P>
<P>
To honor those outstanding experts, China set up the Friendship
Award in the early 1990s. About 40 experts get the award every
year and 395 in all have received it, according to Luo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
