<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Reports Heavy Economic Losses Caused by Kosovo War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has suffered heavy financial
losses to its national economy since NATO began launching air
strikes on Yugoslavia, Trade and Tourism Minister Valentin
Vassilev said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a session of the intergovernmental commission on
limiting and overcoming the impact of the Kosovo crisis, Vassilev
announced that the total amount of economic losses is estimated at
115,800 million leva (78.17 million U.S. dollars) since the start
of NATO's military actions on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Transport, trade, industry and agriculture are among the worst
hit sectors, while tourism is little affected, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria is Yugoslavia's neighbor to the west.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that so far there is no shortage of supplies
and prices remain stable. 
</P>
