<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Film On Former Chinese Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A film about the life of Liu
Shaoqi, who began to serve as the chairman of the People's
Republic of China in 1959, has been completed by the Changchun
Film Studio in northeast China's Jilin Province and will soon be
seen on the China Central Television Station.
</P>
<P>
The film was made by the Radio, Film and Television
Administration's Center for Programs for Film Satellite Channel
and covers an episode in early 1957, when Liu, who was Vice-
chairman of the Communist Party of China Central Committee at the
time, took a special train from Beijing to visit grassroots units
in the South where he dealt with many practical problems in the
lives of ordinary people.
</P>
<P>
Liu is played by Guo Fazeng. The film was directed by Sun Yu as
part of the activities for the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China on October 1, 1949.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shaoqi was born in Ningxiang County, Hunan Province, in
November of 1898 and died in November of 1969. He was elected Vice-
chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
in 1956 and elected chairman of the people's Republic of China in
April of 1959.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
