<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade with Major Asian Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts and
figures about China's foreign trade with major Asian partners in
January-April of 1999, provided by the General Administration of
Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-Japanese trade volume reached 18.81 billion U.S.
dollars, up 7.5 percent from a year earlier. Exports witnessed a
tiny rise of 0.5 percent to 9.25 billion U.S. dollars while
imports went up 15.3 percent to 9.55 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Trade volume with Hong Kong totaled 10.95 billion U.S.
dollars, down 30.1 percent. Exports slumped 34.4 percent to 8.98
billion U.S. dollars while imports down 0.5 percent to 1.97
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Trade volume with the Republic of Korea was 6.9 billion U.S.
dollars, up 4.7 percent. Exports increased 9.5 percent to 2.1
billion U.S. dollars and imports rose 2.7 percent to 4.8 billion U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Trade volume with Taiwan grew 9.5 percent to 6.68 billion U.
S. dollars. Exports went down 3.7 percent to 1.12 billion U.S.
dollars while imports rose 12.6 percent to 5.56 billion U.S.
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
