<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Drugs to Treat Arthritis Developed in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 26 (Xinhua) -- After 9 years' work, Australian
scientists have created a series of drugs to turn off the
inflammatory process that causes tissue and eventual bone
destruction in rheumatoid arthritis and similar diseases.
</P>
<P>
Professor Mark Hogarth, acting director of the Austin Research
Institute, said that it is a platform technology that will pave
the way for the development of drugs to treat allergy and asthma.
</P>
<P>
According to an article published by The Age Wednesday,
Australian scientists have discovered the structure of the Fc
receptor, part of a family of receptors, that plays a crucial role
in the inflammatory process.
</P>
<P>
The Fc receptor acts as a "lock", preventing the release of
inflammatory cells unless they are needed to fight infection.
People with auto-immune diseases have aberrant antibodies which
open the Fc receptor lock, unleashing continuous inflammatory
destruction of tissue.
</P>
<P>
Professor Hogarth said that by knowing the shape of this lock,
they were designing drugs specifically to "plug up" the key hole
of the lock to prevent it being activated.
</P>
<P>
The drugs are being tested in the laboratory and should be
ready for clinical trials in two to three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990526.0293 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Oil Giant Decreasing Production Quota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Daqing Oilfield, China's largest,
in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, has decided to lower
production quotas by 1.2 million tons this year.
</P>
<P>
While cutting quotas, the oilfield will increase efforts to use
natural gas and developing more diverse operations. Sources say
the field will produce 54.5 million tons of crude this year, 500,
000 tons more than the state plan calls for.
</P>
<P>
The oilfield produced 55.7 million tons of oil in 1998 and
local officials say that the adjustment was a strategic step to
improve efficiency and to deal with the gradually shrinking oil
reserves.
</P>
<P>
Daqing expects profits of 11.5 billion yuan in 1999 in spite of
the cut and this will be a rise of 2.87 billion yuan from last
year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Authorities say they believe that the cut will not have a
negative impact on China's strategy of stabilizing oil production
in eastern areas and exploring for more oil reserves in western
areas, but will provide more job opportunities for unemployed
people by building substitute industries and a more diverse
economy.
</P>
<P>
Daqing produces 40 percent of China's continental oil and has
produced 1.5 billion tons of crude since it opened 39 years ago.
It has paid 211.9 billion yuan in taxes.
</P>
<P>
In a similar move, the Liaohe Oilfield and Dagang Oilfield will
also reduce oil production quotas this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
