<HEADLINE> Brazilian President to Attend Rio Group Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Henrique
Cardoso will travel to Mexico City to attend the 13th summit of
the Rio Group scheduled for May 28-29, the Brazilian Foreign
Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group, consisting of Argentina, Brazil, Colombia,
Mexico, Panama, Peru, Uruguay and Venezuela, will discuss
preparations for a Latin American, Caribbean and European Union
summit to be held in June, which will bring together 33 heads of
state and government from Latin America and the Caribbean and 15
from the EU countries.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group summit will also discuss establishing an
association between the South American Common Market (Mercosur)
and the Caribbean. 
