<HEADLINE> Notorious Sri Lankan Gang Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 26 (Xinhua) -- A notorious Sri Lankan gang
allegedly responsible for islandwide crimes ranging from armed
robbery of 220,000 U.S. dollars, stealing of vehicles and dealing
in arms and ammunition have been arrested by the police, police
sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Inspector General of Police N. K. Illangakoon directed
the operations which led to the arrest of the gang leader and
eleven members of the gang Tuesday at Gampaha, 20 kilometers from
Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Police were also able to recover a large cache of arms and
ammunition, allegedly belonging to the gang. Up to Tuesday police
had also recovered over a million Rupees (70 rupees = 1 U.S.
dollar) out of the money robbed by the gang.
</P>
<P>
The leader of the gang is Edward Ranaweera who is suspected to
have led the robbery of 115,000 U.S. dollars from the Veyangoda
Textile Mills recently.
</P>
<P>
Police are in search of another eight persons who are alleged
to be members of the gang but are evading arrest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
