<HEADLINE> Kankkunen Pips Subaru Team Mate Burns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 25 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Juha Kankkunen, in a
Subaru, edged his British team mate Richard Burns by 2.4 seconds
to win the Rally of Argentina in the Cordoba province on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The four-time world champion clocked four hours 17 minutes and
15.4 seconds to record his 22nd rally win, a world record he holds
jointly with Spain's Carlos Sainz.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Didier Auriol in a Toyota secured a podium finish in
third place 39.6 seconds adrift of Kankkunen to join Finn Tommi
Makinen on top of the drivers' standings with 32 points. 
</P>
