<HEADLINE> SW Chinese Province's Tourist Area Covered in Forests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The Xishuangbanna Dai Autonomous
Prefecture, a subtropical tourist site in southwest China's Yunnan
Province, plans to increase its forest coverage from the current
64 percent to 75 percent by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Xishuangbanna is known for its wild animals and plants as well
and colorful ethnic groups living in the vast forests.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture government has raised funds worth nine million
yuan for the ambitious afforestation program, under which local
farmers are asked to reduce the amount of farmland and to plant
more trees.
</P>
<P>
Forest coverage in Xishuangbanna is now above 63 percent, or
124 million hectares, and by 2010, another 300,000 hectares of
trees are scheduled to be planted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
