<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Funds Give Vitality To Industrial City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So far, over 1,700 foreign-funded industrial companies have
been set up in Chongqing, with overseas capital worth a billion U.
S. dollars, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
The investment has come from nearly 30 foreign countries and
regions and over 60 large international companies have a presence
in the city.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the influx of overseas capital has
contributed to the restructuring of local industries, mainly heavy
industries like motorcycle and automobile manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment has also helped technological progress in
the machinery, chemical, pharmaceutical, and instrument industries,
and in light industry, electronics, and building materials.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing was made China's fourth municipality in 1997, after
Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin, giving it provincial-level status
and it is undertaking an ambitious plan to become an economic
center in southwestern China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
