<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Control Project on China's Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 26 (Xinhua) -- The first phase of a flood
control project on the Yellow River has been completed 42 days
ahead of schedule and has passed official review by meeting
standards.
</P>
<P>
Flood control facilities on the Yellow River were listed as one
of the key state projects after last summer's devastating floods
that caused heavy losses of lives and properties.
</P>
<P>
In the flood prevention drive, the central government has
allocated 320 million yuan for the first phase of the project,
which focuses on reinforcing dikes, dredging the river, and flood-
proofing some vulnerable spots.
</P>
<P>
To ensure completion on time, the provincial authorities have
called an engineering team for the project design and all local
governments have been asked to increase flood prevention efforts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
