<HEADLINE> Toe Used To Replace Severed Thumb On Chinese Boy's Hand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 26 (Xinhua) -- Doctors in east China's Anhui
Province have transplanted the toe of 13-year-old Li Wenting, from
Jiangsu Province, to replace a thumb that he lost in an accident
last summer.
</P>
<P>
Surgeons at Hefei's No.1 People's Hospital decided to use the
second toe of his left foot to replace the missing thumb from his
right hand. On May 15, they spent 8 hours cutting off the toe and
aligning blood vessels and nerves near the wound, and putting it
onto the hand.
</P>
<P>
They report that the blood is now circulating well through the
sutured vessels, which is a good sign and the new thumb may be
able to be moved freely in about two weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
