<HEADLINE> Wild Animals Set Free in Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 40,000 birds, snakes,
frogs, squirrels, tortoises, fish, and other animals were set free
Monday in the city of Dandong in northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The activity was sponsored by an urban association that spent
over 10,000 yuan (1,200 U.S. dollars) buying the animals from
individuals. A local hi-tech development joint venture established
the association in 1996 with the theme of protecting wildlife and
the environment.
</P>
<P>
The nonprofit-making association has 16,000 domestic and
overseas members and has spent more than 40,000 yuan setting 70,
000 captive animals free in recent years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
