<HEADLINE> UNDP to Hear Report on Cambodia Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 25 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) goodwill ambassador Misako Konno is to report her
trip to Cambodia on Wednesday to help draw international attention
to development needs in the country, U.N. sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Konno began a five-day tour of Cambodia on May 20, which took
her to the sites of UNDP-supported community development,
resettlement and poverty alleviation projects and a U.N. mine
action program, according to a UNDP weekly.
</P>
<P>
Konno is scheduled to meet UNDP Administrator James Gustave
Speth in New York on Wednesday and their talks are expected to
focus on the development challenges posed by landmines and the
social and economic needs of displaced persons returning home.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian Government said early this year that it needs one
billion U.S. dollars a year from outside including foreign
investment and international aid to kickstart its economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
